    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>An Inconvenient Woman</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Dana Korbman letter expresses disappointment at choice of David France's article on transsexual Calpernia Sarah Addams and murder of Pfc Barry Winchell for Memorial Day weekend cover story</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>I was a bit disappointed with your choice of a cover article for the Sunday of Memorial Day weekend. With fewer Americans enlisting in the armed services today, and with fewer Americans having been personally touched by the tragedy of war, it seems that you might have chosen to remind your readers of the holiday's significance by honoring the young men and women who have fallen victim to the misfortunes of combat and perhaps saved this worthwhile yet extremely controversial subject for another weekend.</p>
        <p>Dana Korbman</p>
        <p>Highland Park, N.J.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
